				\begin{document}$${\text{E}} = {{(\Delta e \times {{u}_{s}})} \mathord{\left/ {\vphantom {{(\Delta e \times {{u}_{s}})} p}} \right. \kern-0em} p},$$\end{document}where Δe is the difference between water vapor pressures in the chamber with and without a leaf, expressed in mbar; us is the rate of air flow in the leaf chamber, mol/m2 s; and p is atmospheric pressure, mbar.

The rate of water vapor flow through the stomata (stomatal conductance, gs) was calculated as the reciprocal of the stomatal resistance (gs = 1/rs). Stomatal resistance, in turn, was found by the formula7\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
