Respiration rate and contributions of individual respiratory pathways. The rate of leaf respiration was determined polarographically from O2 uptake at 20°С using an Oxytherm system (Hansatech Instruments, United Kingdom). Leaf cuts from the middle part of freshly harvested leaf blades were placed in the reaction vessel containing HEPES buffer (50 mM, pH 7.2, Helicon, Russia). The samples were constantly stirred during the measurements. Activities of individual respiratory pathways were determined with the use of specific inhibitors, whose optimal concentrations were chosen in preliminary experiments. An 8 mM solution of salicylhydroxamic acid (SHAM) (Lancaster, United Kingdom) was used as an inhibitor of alternative oxidase (AOX). Cytochrome oxidase activity was inhibited with 2 mM KCN solution (Sigma, United States). The total rate of oxygen uptake was expressed as the sum of individual components and expressed in nmol O2/g DW min:8\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${{V}_{{\text{t}}}} = {{V}_{{{\text{alt}}}}} + {{V}_{{{\text{cyt}}}}} + {{V}_{{{\text{res}}}}},$$\end{document}where Vt is total respiration; Valt is alternative respiration sensitive to SHAM, an inhibitor of alternative oxidase; Vcyt is cyanide-sensitive (cytochrome-dependent) respiration; and Vres is the residual respiration recorded in the presence of inhibitors for the alternative pathway (AP) and the cytochrome pathway (CP). The determinations were carried out in five to eight biological replicates.

Evaluation of the pro-/antioxidant status of leaves. The activity of lipid peroxidation was assessed by the content of thiobarbituric acid reactive substances (TBARS) [18]. The amount of TBARS was calculated on the basis of the extinction coefficient after subtracting nonspecific absorbance at 600 nm. The H2O2 content was determined using xylenol orange [19]. The specificity was tested by the inhibition of H2O2 formation upon the addition of catalase (Sigma, United States). The content of superoxide anion radical (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
